<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-20T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/8–2045</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d102fn1">In telegram 3020, August 23, 1945, 2
                                p.m., Ambassador Harriman reported that “Vyshinski under date of
                                August 21 acknowledged my letter of August 20 but offered no
                                comments.” (868.00/8–2345) Audrey Yanuaryevich Vishinsky was First
                                Assistant People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-20T12:00:00+03:00">August 20,
                                    1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 20—4:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2960. Dept’s 1777, Aug 9 and 1868, Aug 19. Substance of communiqué on
                            supervision Greek elections and reassuring observations contained in
                            Dept’s 1861 Aug 18 have been communicated to Molotov in letter this
                            morning.</p>
                        <p>To Dept 2960, rptd Athens 42, London 415, Paris 315.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>